  <h2>Run it yourself</h2>
  <p>
    Self-hosting is a right here, not a dare: one binary, a
    &euro;4-a-month box, about ten minutes, certificates and updates
    handled for you. It has <a href="/self-host/">its own page</a>, with
    the actual commands.
  </p>

  <h2>Watch it run</h2>
  <p>
    The live fleet — capacity, services, versions rolling out — is public
    at <a href="https://status.elevenmessenger.com">status.elevenmessenger.com</a>,
    part of <a href="/openness/">the openness charter</a>. The philosophy
    of building this way is
    <a href="https://11factor.org">The Eleven Factors</a> — a serious
    parody of 12factor.net.
  </p>

  <p class="fine">
    And yes, obviously: zsh.
  </p>
